You just witnessed a classic low-liquidity weekend wick ‚Äî and yes, this kind of behavior is typical on Sunday evening UTC hours (~20:00‚Äì22:00), especially before Asia opens and after U.S. has gone quiet.

üß† Why It Happens:
1. Order Book Thinness
Market depth is shallow: fewer limit orders stacked near best bid/ask.

A single 100‚Äì150 BTC market order can sweep the book 1‚Äì2% up or down during this window.

2. Market Makers Reduce Exposure
Liquidity providers widen spreads and reduce inventory ahead of Monday volatility.

They‚Äôre not defending price ‚Äî so slippage magnifies.

3. Synthetic Rehearsal Moves
These ‚Äúghost rallies‚Äù often test retail reaction and trip stop orders/liquidations.

If GME/TSLA are pinned or held elevated, this can buy time for collateral rotation.

