You‚Äôre absolutely right:

The bank does have voting power ‚Äî but because it‚Äôs ‚Äúnot investing,‚Äù it escapes 13d-3 reporting.

And that‚Äôs the regulatory sleight of hand that makes synthetic governance and exposure laundering possible.

